1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,320
Bathing Micky
(??? )

2
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:19,910
We are all born,
我們出生，

3
00:00:20,010 --> 00:00:22,680
and eventually we all die,
然後我們死亡

4
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:26,960
that is how it has all been planned.
這全部都是計畫好的。

5
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:29,981
You don't know when it will happen...
你不知道什麼時候會發生.....

6
00:00:30,081 --> 00:00:32,599
And thinking about it is of no use.
想這件事情也是沒意義。

7
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:39,880
To paraphrase Socrates:
套用蘇格拉底所說的話；

8
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,208
"If death is but a long sleep,
如果死亡只不過是一個漫長的睡眠，

9
00:00:43,308 --> 00:00:46,239
it must be a wonderful thing."
它一定是一個美妙的事情。

10
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:50,200
One should never fear the unknown.
一個人不應該畏懼不知道的事物。

11
00:00:58,280 --> 00:00:59,707
He was fun,
他很風趣，

12
00:00:59,807 --> 00:01:02,799
and always in a good mood.
總是有著好心情。

13
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:06,298
And he was very intelligent.
他非常的聰明。

14
00:01:06,398 --> 00:01:10,919
He would write songs and speeches...
他會寫歌、詞.....

15
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:15,000
He was always looking for fun and games.
他總是在開玩笑和遊戲。

16
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:17,459
And that was great,
那真的很棒，

17
00:01:17,559 --> 00:01:21,919
because no one likes a curmudgeon.
因為沒有人喜歡一個倔老頭。

18
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:40,871
Love is having someone
愛就是擁有一個

19
00:01:40,971 --> 00:01:45,239
you enjoy being with...
你喜歡和他相處在一起的人...

20
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:47,880
Someone who...
有一個....

21
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:55,625
Someone whose company you
一個帶給你快樂

22
00:01:55,725 --> 00:01:59,159
really enjoy and who brings you joy.
和享受他的陪伴。

23
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:00,762
Someone who is interested
一個和你

24
00:02:00,862 --> 00:02:02,599
in the same things as you,
有著相同的喜好

25
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,990
and with whom you enjoy
並讓你享受

26
00:02:05,090 --> 00:02:06,960
your daily life.
你每天的生活。

27
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:13,840
I believe that to be very important.
我相信這非常的重要。

28
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:17,262
And then there is the sexual aspect.
當然這其中還有著性。

29
00:02:17,362 --> 00:02:20,879
That's usually how it all begins...
通常這就是一切的開始....

30
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:42,983
When we got married
我們剛結婚時，

31
00:02:43,083 --> 00:02:44,839
we didn't want children
我們並不想要小孩。

32
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:48,130
because my husband was Jewish
因為我的丈夫是猶太人，

33
00:02:48,230 --> 00:02:51,479
and Hitler had occupied Denmark.
希特勒佔領了丹麥。

34
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:15,306
When I woke up on 9th April, 1940,
當我在1940年4月9日起床時，

35
00:03:15,406 --> 00:03:18,959
there was a terrible racket.
一個很可怕的聲響。

36
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:20,329
I went to the window
我跑去窗戶

37
00:03:20,429 --> 00:03:22,799
and opened the blinds to have a look
旁打開百葉窗....

38
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:26,890
- and the sky was filled with planes,
從滿是飛機的天空

39
00:03:26,990 --> 00:03:30,559
dropping something from the air.
中掉了東西下來。

40
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:40,472
It was unreal.
一點都不真實，

41
00:03:40,572 --> 00:03:44,999
It was like a bolt from the blue.
好似晴天霹靂。

42
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:49,400
It was like a sudden slap to the face.
就好似被打了一巴掌。

43
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:51,703
It was... We didn't know
我們不知道

44
00:03:51,803 --> 00:03:53,799
what was happening.
發生了什麼事。

45
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:03,354
They would transport Jews on trucks
他們會把猶太人載

46
00:04:03,454 --> 00:04:06,079
and load them onto ships.
上卡車，在運上船。

47
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:08,473
We didn't know how bad
我們不知道

48
00:04:08,573 --> 00:04:11,759
the concentration camps were.
集中營到底是怎樣。

49
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:22,193
There were rumours that, where a Jew
有傳言，一個猶太人娶了

50
00:04:22,293 --> 00:04:25,399
was married to a non-Jewish person -
一個非猶太人

51
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:27,431
- you would both be okay.
你們兩個可能會沒事。

52
00:04:27,531 --> 00:04:30,079
At least that's what the Germans said -
至少德國人是這樣說

53
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:32,582
- but no one believed them.
但沒人相信。

54
00:04:32,682 --> 00:04:36,639
We then received word from a "good" German
我們接著從好德國人那得到消息

55
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:42,320
- that on a certain day in October -
在十月的某一天，

56
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:46,880
all the Jews were going to be rounded up.
所有的猶太人被集中起來。

57
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,495
I was guilty of miscegenation
???? 通婚

58
00:05:01,595 --> 00:05:03,479
because I had married a Jew.
我因為和一個猶太人結婚。

59
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:06,191
That was a term they used to
他們有一個專業名詞

60
00:05:06,291 --> 00:05:09,439
describe those who were not Aryans
來描寫那些非亞利安人

61
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:14,760
 the race that they were so fond of.
他們是如此的尊敬那個種族。

62
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:37,028
It wasn't a time we enjoyed,
對猶太人來說，

63
00:05:37,128 --> 00:05:41,119
with the things they had against the Jews.
這段時間並不是那麼的美好。

64
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:46,600
If we had a child together...
假如我們有了孩子....

65
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:49,244
Supposedly, it was the mother
據說，這是母親的決定....

66
00:05:49,344 --> 00:05:51,989
who determined it... But we thought...
但我們認為....

67
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:54,188
We didn't trust the Germans,
我們不相信德國人，

68
00:05:54,288 --> 00:05:57,519
and the child of course would be half-Jewish.
而且我們的小孩是半個猶太人。

69
00:05:57,640 --> 00:06:01,080
So we decided not to have a child.
所以我們決定不要生小孩。

70
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:51,800
That was wonderful!
真的是太棒了!

71
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:01,280
A friend of my husband, Henrik Kraft -
我丈夫的一個朋友, Henrik Kraft

72
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:03,517
knew Leif B. Hendil,
認識 Leif B. Hendil。

73
00:07:03,617 --> 00:07:05,999
the editor of Ekstra Bladet.
Ekstrabladet 的編輯

74
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:08,975
They were behind the evacuation of Jews
他們在背地裡主持著將猶太人

75
00:07:09,075 --> 00:07:12,479
from Snekkersten to Helsingborg.
從 Snekkersten 移動到 Helsingborg。

76
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:15,806
They had completed 30 crossings.
他們已經成功完成30次。

77
00:07:15,906 --> 00:07:19,039
We were due to go on the next one.
我們本來是下一梯。

78
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:36,120
That really was wonderful.
那真的是很美好。

79
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:43,680
The night in question turned into a nightmare.
出事情的那晚成了噩夢。

80
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,885
Suddenly, the engine cut out
突然，引擎不動了，

81
00:07:45,985 --> 00:07:48,239
and the boat started bobbing about.
船開始漂。

82
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:50,860
We shouted: "What is going on?"
"發生了什麼事?"我們喊著。

83
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:53,239
All the men were lying on deck.
所有人都趴在甲板上。

84
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:56,400
They told us it was a German patrol boat -
他們告訴我們是一艘德國巡邏船，

85
00:07:56,520 --> 00:08:00,135
and to avoid them seeing us on the radar
為了不被他們的雷達發現，

86
00:08:00,235 --> 00:08:03,159
they'd switched off the engine.
他們必須要把引擎關掉。

87
00:08:12,080 --> 00:08:15,080
After 15 minutes we heard this sound...
15分鐘過後，我們聽到聲音...

88
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:18,680
And we knew, we could breathe a sigh of relief.
我們知道，我們可以鬆一口氣。

89
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:32,161
We spent two years "over there".
從1943年10月到1945年，

90
00:08:32,261 --> 00:08:35,199
From October 1943 till 1945.
我們花了兩年時間在那邊。

91
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:37,338
We became more optimistic
我們變得更加樂觀，

92
00:08:37,438 --> 00:08:40,519
as things started going against Hitler.
因為局勢開始對希特勒不利。

93
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:42,700
That kept us going.
這件事情驅使著我們繼續下去。

94
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:46,039
We knew it was only a question of time.
我們知道只是時間上的問題。

95
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:01,053
We got married in '32,
我們在1932年結婚，

96
00:09:01,153 --> 00:09:03,119
and for 10-15 years
在結婚的10-15年間

97
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:07,400
we tried our best to avoid having any children.
我們試著去避免生小孩。

98
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:14,320
When we returned home in 1945 -
當我們在1945年回家時

99
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:16,480
- we decided the time had come -
我們決定時候到了，

100
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:19,370
- and our first child was born in 1946,
我們的第一個小孩在1946年出生，

101
00:09:19,470 --> 00:09:21,399
followed by one more in 1948.
下一個在1948年。

102
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:46,610
Timer has been set to 9 seconds...
時間設定倒數九秒，

103
00:09:46,710 --> 00:09:50,360
And Micky, remember to smile.
還有Micky 記得要微笑。

104
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:53,000
I always look foolish in photographs...
我相片中總是看起來笨笨的...

105
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:56,168
That's because you always keep talking.
那是因為你總是在說話。

106
00:09:56,268 --> 00:09:57,919
Let's take one more.
我們在拍一張。

107
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:15,121
The most difficult thing for me is
對我來說最困難的事是

108
00:10:15,221 --> 00:10:17,679
that my husband has passed away
我丈夫的過世

109
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:20,396
and so have all my best friends
還有過去50年間所有

110
00:10:20,496 --> 00:10:22,399
from the past 50 years.
我最好的朋友。

111
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:26,000
That is why it is important to have a hobby -
這是為什麼要有個興趣

112
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,948
because you'll meet people
因為你會遇見比

113
00:10:28,048 --> 00:10:29,599
younger than yourself.
你年輕的人。

114
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:32,435
I have been lucky that way,
我已經很幸運了，

115
00:10:32,535 --> 00:10:36,479
because I have made many friends here.
因為我在這認識了很多朋友。

116
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:52,840
My mother-in-law was 94 when she died.
我婆婆在94歲時過世。

117
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:55,766
She'd say: "The most difficult part
她說過"最令人傷心的事情是所有

118
00:10:55,866 --> 00:10:58,280
is that all my friends have died
我的朋友都過世了，

119
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,877
and that I have no one left
沒有人可以和我一起

120
00:10:59,977 --> 00:11:01,759
to talk to from those days".
聊著那些過去的日子。"

121
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:05,255
There is no one to share
沒有人可以分享

122
00:11:05,355 --> 00:11:09,159
all the good memories with.
所有的美好回憶。

123
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:13,720
That's just the way it is.
事情就只是這樣。

124
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:18,920
There she is! "Tres elegant"...
她在那!

125
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:22,640
100 YEARS OLD
100歲

126
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:51,779
Getting older is a fact of life
變老是生命中一個

127
00:11:51,879 --> 00:11:53,919
which you cannot change
你無法改變的事實，

128
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,557
- so you might as well try
所以你不妨去試

129
00:11:55,657 --> 00:11:57,359
to enjoy it as much as you can.
著享受看看。

130
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:59,748
Try to keep doing the things
嘗試繼續做

131
00:11:59,848 --> 00:12:01,639
you've always done
你一直在做的事情

132
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,537
- which is what I do.
這是我做的。

133
00:12:03,637 --> 00:12:05,479
I keep participating.
我盡量去參與。

134
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:08,112
Keep participating in daily life
只要你可以，

135
00:12:08,212 --> 00:12:11,119
for as long as you possibly can.
盡量去參與你的日常生活。

136
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:13,840
I believe that is very important.
我相信這是非常重要的。
